Sofía Margarita Vergara Vergara -LRB- -LSB- soˈfi.a βerˈɣaɾa -RSB- ; born July 10 , 1972 -RRB- is a Colombian-American actress and model .
Vergara rose to prominence while co-hosting two television shows for Spanish-language television network Univisión in the late 1990s .
Her first notable acting job in English was in the film Chasing Papi -LRB- 2003 -RRB- .
Subsequently , she appeared in other films , including Four Brothers -LRB- 2005 -RRB- and two Tyler Perry films : Meet the Browns -LRB- 2008 -RRB- and Madea Goes to Jail -LRB- 2009 -RRB- , receiving an ALMA Award nomination for the latter .
Vergara 's success on television has earned her roles in films The Smurfs -LRB- 2011 -RRB- , New Year 's Eve -LRB- 2011 -RRB- , Happy Feet Two -LRB- 2011 -RRB- , The Three Stooges -LRB- 2012 -RRB- , Escape from Planet Earth -LRB- 2013 -RRB- , Machete Kills -LRB- 2013 -RRB- , Chef -LRB- 2014 -RRB- , and Hot Pursuit -LRB- 2015 -RRB- .
In 2012 , 2013 , and 2016 , she was the top-earning actress on US television .
Vergara stars on the ABC series Modern Family as Gloria Delgado-Pritchett , for which she has been nominated for four Golden Globe Awards , four Primetime Emmy Awards , and seven Screen Actors Guild Awards .
In 2014 , she was ranked as the 32nd most powerful woman in the world by Forbes .